.TH lsfirewirephy 8 "15 Aug 2010" "@PACKAGE_STRING@" 
.IX lsfirewirephy
.SH NAME
lsfirewirephy \- list PHYs of FireWire devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lsfirewirephy
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B lsfirewirephy
utility prints the device IDs of the PHYs of the FireWire devices on a bus.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-d, \-\-device=" file
Specifies the FireWire bus that should be listed.
.
This must be the device file of the FireWire controller
that is connected to the bus.
.IP
If not specified, the default is
.BR /dev/fw0 .
.TP
.BI "\-p, \-\-phy-id=" nr
Instead of listing all devices on the bus,
list only the device with the specified index.
.
The index is 0-based and cannot be larger than 62.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a summary of the command-line options and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version number of
.B lsfirewirephy
on the standard output and exit.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs to <@PACKAGE_BUGREPORT@>.
.br
@PACKAGE_NAME@ home page: <@PACKAGE_URL@>.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lsfirewire (8)
